  "texts": [
    "Chen and Chang (2012) proposed the hybrid approach as a three-phase categorization method that includes SVM, K-means, and KNN algorithms.",
    "In this approach, they used TF-IDF to select discriminative terms to classify 9062 patent documents as test datasets (12,042 for training) and the best result for the model was 53.25% accuracy at the sub-group level (Chen and Chang, 2012).",
    "Tran and Kavuluru (2017) explore text data and machine learning-based classification in the context of the CPC system.",
    "Such exercises build on earlier work of automated patent classification for IPC classes (Fall et al., 2003).",
    "Grawe et al. (2017) introduce deep learning and word embedding methods for text-based patent classification."
  ],
